The paper deals with zero-shot visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves adversarial learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves disentangling semantic spaces, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper evaluates its proposed method on popular benchmarks, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves classification and reconstruction, which are common tasks in natural language processing (cs.CL).
